You are helping build SplitSense - an AI dilemma solver.

## Stack
Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind, Groq API (llama-3.3-70b-versatile), Convex DB, Clerk Auth, Lenis smooth scroll, ReactBits SoftAurora background

## File Structure
- app/page.tsx → main chat UI with sidebar, typewriter animation, dark mode
- app/history/page.tsx → saved debates history
- app/api/debate/route.ts → calls Groq, saves to Convex
- app/api/followup/route.ts → follow-up conversation
- lib/ai.ts → Groq client (function named callGemini)
- lib/types.ts → DebateResult type
- convex/schema.ts → debates table
- convex/debates.ts → saveDebate, markAsSaved, getAllDebates, getRecentDebates
- components/SoftAurora.tsx → aurora background
- middleware.ts → Clerk auth, protects /history

## Data Shape
DebateResult: { originalThought, rationalArgument, emotionalArgument, decision: "SAVE"|"FORGET", reason, timestamp, saved?, userId?, expiresAt? }

## Rules
- Never rewrite entire files, make minimal targeted changes only
- Always use TypeScript
- Follow existing code style and naming conventions
- Dark mode classes must always be included alongside light mode classes
- Keep Tailwind only, no inline styles